#: src/install.md:1
msgid "Installing Helix"
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:3
msgid ""
"The typical way to install Helix is via [your operating system's package "
"manager](./package-managers.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:5
msgid "Note that:"
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:7
msgid ""
"To get the latest nightly version of Helix, you need to [build from source]"
"(./building-from-source.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:10
msgid ""
"To take full advantage of Helix, install the language servers for your "
"preferred programming languages. See the [wiki](https://github.com/helix-"
"editor/helix/wiki/Language-Server-Configurations) for instructions."
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:15
msgid "Pre-built binaries"
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:17
msgid ""
"Download pre-built binaries from the [GitHub Releases page](https://github."
"com/helix-editor/helix/releases). The tarball contents include an `hx` "
"binary and a `runtime` directory. To set up Helix:"
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:21
msgid ""
"Add the `hx` binary to your system's `$PATH` to allow it to be used from the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:22
msgid ""
"Copy the `runtime` directory to a location that `hx` searches for runtime "
"files. A typical location on Linux/macOS is `~/.config/helix/runtime`."
msgstr ""

#: src/install.md:24
msgid ""
"To see the runtime directories that `hx` searches, run `hx --health`. If "
"necessary, you can override the default runtime location by setting the "
"`HELIX_RUNTIME` environment variable."
msgstr ""
